  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink238-kilavi">varaiyātu vantoḻukum talaimakaṉukk ivaḷ kaviṉ nī vantakālattu varutalāl nī pōṉa kālatt ataṉ tolaiv uṉakk aṟiyappaṭāt eṉat tōḻi colli varaivukaṭāyatu.  </p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> The confidante urging marriage, saying to the hero who keeps coming without marrying:
          “Because her beauty returns when you arrive,
          its loss when you depart is not known to you.”
          
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink238">
<l>vārkōṭṭu vayattakar vārātu māṟiṉuṅ</l>
<l>kurumayirp puruvai yācaiyi ṉalku</l>
<l>māa laruvit taṇperuñ cilampa</l>
<l>nīyivaṇ varūuṅ kālai</l>
<l>mēvaru mātōviva ṇalaṉē teyyō</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>O man from the slopes of the cool, great mountain with large waterfalls,</l>
        <l>where the bright-fleeced ewe remains with desire,</l>
        <l>even if the long-horned strong ram does not come and turns away—</l>
        <l>when you come here, her beauty will cling [to her].</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
